form(method='post' action='./')
  div
    section#introduction
      h2 Boodle introduction
    p
      | Boodle is your new tool to help make your study life easier. An easy
      | and quick guide on how to setup this tool will follow.
  section#guide
    h2 Guide on how to setup Boodle
  p 
    | Now you have to find your personal Moodle token, you need to login to
		|			Moodle first, and then click on your name in the top right side of the
		|			webpage.
    |
		|			Then click preferences in the top down menu and you will be met with a
		|			lot of different options.
    |
		|			From here you have to click on the security keys option, which will
		|			lead you to a site with 3 keys. The key that is needed for the bot is
		|			the bottom one also called "Moodle mobile web service".
    |
		|			Copy and paste this into the input field on the website.
    |
		|			If you dont want to use the bot anymore, you can just click the reset
		|			bottom on Moodle and the bot will not work until you input the new
		|			Moodle token.<br /><br />
  .form-group
    label#name-label.name-label(for='name') Moodle token
    input#postDiscordId.form-control(type='text' name='DiscordId' readonly='' value=`${id}`)
    input#postMoodletoken.form-control(type='text' name='MoodleToken' placeholder='Enter your Moodle token' required='')
  .form-group
    button#btnSubmit.submit-button(type='submit' formmethod='post')
      | Submit
    p This will connect the Moodle token to this discord id: #{id}
  section#commands
    h2 Commands for Boodle
    p
      | In this section you will see all the possible commands that you can
      | use with Boodle on Discord.
